{"body": "I have to agree with @drogus that normal `if / unless` seem to be enough in this case. And you can always use something like this instead of wrapping in if/unless:\r\n\r\n```erb\r\n  <% cache [ @user, 'form' ] do %>\r\n    ...\r\n  <% end unless @user.changed? %>\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe that the `:if / :unless` options wouldn't help that much in that example of `unless/else` you've used, so normal ruby should win in this case, right? Thanks :)", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4489066", "created_at": "2012-03-13T23:37:46Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5396#issuecomment-4489066", "updated_at": "2012-03-13T23:37:46Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5396, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523818cbbd3543c15100e0cd"}, "id": 4489066, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/